<h2 id="heading-24">Common Tech Stack Mistakes</h2>

<h3 id="heading-25">The "All-in-One" Trap</h3>

<p>Tools like "Brex" or "Pilot" promise everything but deliver complexity. You're better off with best-in-class tools that integrate well.</p>

<h3 id="heading-26">Over-Investing in Shiny Features</h3>

<p>Don't pay for features you won't use. Start simple and add complexity only when you need it.</p>

<h3 id="heading-27">Ignoring Mobile Access</h3>

<p>If your tool doesn't work on mobile, your team won't use it consistently.</p>

<h3 id="heading-28">Forgetting About Training</h3>

<p>The best tech stack fails without proper training. Budget 4-8 hours for team training.</p>

