<h2 id="heading-34">Measuring Success</h2>

<p>Track these metrics to ensure your stack is working:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Reconciliation time:</strong> Should be under 4 hours/month</li>
<li><strong>Expense report errors:</strong> Under 2% of submissions</li>
<li><strong>Invoice collection time:</strong> Under 30 days</li>
<li><strong>Financial report timeliness:</strong> Available within 3 days of month-end</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="heading-35">The Bottom Line</h2>

<p>The right tech stack doesn't eliminate bookkeeping - it makes it efficient and accurate. Focus on tools that integrate well, are easy to use, and scale with your business.</p>

<p>Start with QuickBooks Online, add bank connections and expense management, then layer in specialized tools as you grow.</p>

<p>The goal isn't to have the most tools. It's to have the right tools that make your financial life simpler, not more complicated.</p>